  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "uzi1hF7SHpKFVlUwBRY/sq4wzSg=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:47.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "The integration decomposes into three layers with clear seams:\n\n**Layer 1 \u2014 `bee-reactor-adapter` (npm)**: the `SwarmClient` class wraps the Bee SDK. It exposes `uploadData`/`downloadData` for encrypted `/bytes`, `uploadFile`/`downloadFile` for ACT-protected `/bzz`, `createGrantees`/`patchGrantees` for ACT grantee lists, `pssSend`/`pssSubscribe` for 1-to-1 messaging, `gsocSend`/`gsocSubscribe` for sub-second notifications, and manifest helpers (`updateManifest`, `readManifest`, `updateDriveManifest`, `updateUserManifest`). It also handles per-topic write locks, 3-retry backoff on feed writes, and auto-detects reference vs inline feed format.\n\n**Layer 2 \u2014 SwarmChannel**: a native `IChannel` implementation wired via `ReactorBuilder.withSync()` and a `CompositeChannelFactory` that routes `\"swarm\"` and `\"gql\"` config types to the right sub-factory. Owns push (outbox) and pull (inbox), cursor tracking via `sync_cursors`, and dead letters via `sync_dead_letters`.\n\n**Layer 3 \u2014 Connect UI**: the `swarm-settings/` panel shows connection status, stamp health, doc tree with sync badges, and share/import controls; the `components/chat/` panel ships the chat UI.\n\nThe plugin layer still owns Bee detection, stamp selection, wallet key derivation, and UI event emission.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:47.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:47.000Z"
    }
  },
